The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, May 28: Orissa chief minister Navin Patnaik said Poscos planned $12-billion steel complex in the state is on track. Poscos chief financial officer Lee Dong-hee said in Seoul last week the company would start building the steel complex in October despite local opposition. There are only teething problems, we expect everything to fall in place as soon as possible, Patnaik said.

 Mumbai, May 28: The Bombay Stock Exchange today crossed the $1-trillion milestone in terms of market capitalisation of all the companies listed on the bourse. The combined market value of all the firms listed on BSE rose to Rs 40,52,121.32 crore.

 New Delhi, May 28: Tata Consultancy Services (TCS) will consolidate its financial products into a single business unit, TCS Financial Solutions. The unit will function as a products company within the TCS family.

 New Delhi, May 28: Reliance Communications (R-Com) today appointed JP Morgan as the merchant banker to look for strategic buyers for its wholly owned tower subsidiary, Reliance Telecom Infrastructure.

 New Delhi, May 28: SAIL will invest Rs 43,000 crore till 2010 to nearly double its manufacturing capacity to 24.98 million tonnes from 13 mt now.




